def: A Latin adverb and preposition, signifying against, contrary,in opposition, etc., entering as a prefix into the composition ofmany English words. Cf. Counter, adv. & pref.
To convert into a province or provinces. [Obs.] Howell.
Worthy of being wished for; desirable. [Obs.] Puller.
A condition of lowered functional activity, without visiblestructural change, produced in an organ by a shock, as by fall orblow; as, a concussion of the brain.
Like a rasp, or the sound made by a rasp; grating. R. D.Blackmore.
To put out of phase, as two parts of a single alternatingcurrent.
A rare zeolitic mineral occurring in white monoclinic crystalswith pearly luster. It is a hydrous silicate of aluminia, baryta, andstrontia.
